Britain will always be open to those who want to live, work and build a life here.
However, it is not right that people who do not live in the United Kingdom, as well as foreign companies, should be able to buy homes more easily than the British working class.
The dream of owning a home has become too difficult for many people and the humiliation of sleeping on the streets is still too real."
