The European team won the 2018 Ryder Cup, defeating the American team 16.5 to 10.5 at Le Golf National, outside Paris, France.
The United States has now suffered six consecutive defeats on European soil since its last win in the Ryder Cup in Europe in 1993.
Europe reclaimed the crown when the Danish team of Thomas Bjorn won 14.5 points to beat the United States.
American golfer Phil Mickelson, who had to fight most of the tournament, hit his tee shot into the water on the par-3 16th hole, admitting defeat to Francesco Molinari.
