American Jordan Spieth fell to defeat by 5 and 4 to the lowest-ranked player on the European team, Denmark's Thorbjorn Olesen.
World number one Dustin Johnson lost 2 and 1 to Englishman Ian Poulter, who could have played his last Ryder Cup.
